snippet.textDisplay:
You already know you were allergic to the eyebrow tint, as soon as it started stinging you should have stopped the process, washed it off and not gone any further, especially since you know the symptoms may not show up until later.

I have allergies to dye; I know whatever the patch test results are that I'd probably have a reaction when actually doing the process.

And your eyes aren't dissolving; they're irritated because of the reaction. 🙄

They'll be fine, just don't rub them, stop pulling the lid down, just lay a cold, damn flannel over them and it should take away some of the redness and give some relief.

snippet.textDisplay:
All it takes to develop an allergy is exposure and re-exposure. And the more you expose yourself to it, the more chance there is that your reaction escalates.

Take Benadryl. Swelling probably went down after your shower because you basically flushed your eyes. Maybe a warm wash cloth would help? 🤷🏻‍♀️

If you’re allergic to dyes, though, you should carry Benadryl with you everywhere. Imagine going into a shop, trying on a dress, and then morphing into an angry, itchy version of the Michelin man because you’re allergic to the dye.

snippet.textDisplay: Always go to your beauty therapist if you have a reaction! they can point you in the right direction. I'm a beauty therapist, and have seen this many times on other peoples clients. Under your eyeball it looks like bruising/irritation from the eyepad and products used- that should go down in a couple of days - its nothing to worry about. Take some allergy tablets, and put a cold compress on your eyes to reduce the swelling. if this doesn't go down, go to the doctors and seek further medical help :)
